SIMPLE: purpureo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purpureo-
<hw>Pur*pu"re*o-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A combining form signifying
<xex>of a purple</xex> or <xex>purple-red color</xex>. Specif.
<fld>(Chem.)</fld>, used in designating certain brilliant
<xex>purple-red</xex> compounds of cobaltic chloride and ammonia,
similar to the roseocobaltic compounds. See <er>Cobaltic</er>.
</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1166 --></p>

<p><ent>Purpuric</ent>⟦br⟧
